## Configuration-Driven Behaviors

### Offset Reset Policy (`auto.offset.reset`)

**Applies When**: No committed offset found for partition.

```properties
auto.offset.reset=earliest    # Start from beginning
auto.offset.reset=latest      # Start from end
auto.offset.reset=none        # Throw NoOffsetForPartitionException
```

### Commit Behavior (`enable.auto.commit`, `auto.commit.interval.ms`)

```properties
enable.auto.commit=true       # Automatic commits (default)
auto.commit.interval.ms=5000  # Every 5 seconds

enable.auto.commit=false      # Manual commits only
```

### Poll Timeout and Batch Size

```properties
fetch.max.wait.ms=500       # Broker waits up to 500ms for batch
fetch.min.bytes=1           # Minimum bytes to return
max.poll.records=500        # Max records per poll
```

### Heartbeat and Session

```properties
heartbeat.interval.ms=3000         # Send heartbeat every 3 seconds
session.timeout.ms=10000           # Die if no heartbeat for 10 seconds
max.poll.interval.ms=300000        # Die if no poll for 5 minutes
```

### Isolation Level

```properties
isolation.level=read_uncommitted   # Read all messages (default)
isolation.level=read_committed     # Skip aborted transactions
```

With `read_committed`:
- `poll()` filters out aborted transaction messages
- `seekToEnd()` seeks to LSO (Last Stable Offset)
- `endOffsets()` returns LSO
- Transactional messages have gaps in offsets

