## Common Patterns and Best Practices

### Pattern 1: Simple Group-Managed Consumer

```java
Properties props = new Properties();
props.setProperty("bootstrap.servers", "localhost:9092");
props.setProperty("group.id", "my-group");
props.setProperty("key.deserializer", "org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer");
props.setProperty("value.deserializer", "org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer");
props.setProperty("auto.offset.reset", "earliest");

try (KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props)) {
    consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

    while (true) {
        ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
        for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
            System.out.printf("offset = %d, key = %s, value = %s%n",
                record.offset(), record.key(), record.value());
        }
    }
}
```

### Pattern 2: Manual Offset Management

```java
props.setProperty("enable.auto.commit", "false");

try (KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props)) {
    consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

    while (true) {
        ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));

        for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
            try {
                processRecord(record);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                handleError(record, e);
            }
        }

        // Commit when batch is done
        consumer.commitSync();
    }
}
```

### Pattern 3: Exactly-Once Semantics with External Store

```java
props.setProperty("enable.auto.commit", "false");

try (KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props)) {
    consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"), new ConsumerRebalanceListener() {
        @Override
        public void onPartitionsRevoked(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
            // Commit current state + offsets together
            saveState();
        }

        @Override
        public void onPartitionsAssigned(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
            // Restore state from external store
            restoreState();
        }
    });

    while (true) {
        ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));

        // Process in transaction with state update
        try {
            processRecordsInTransaction(records);
            commitStateAndOffsets(records);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            rollbackState();
        }
    }
}
```

### Pattern 4: Single Consumer Thread + Worker Pool

```java
int numWorkers = 8;
BlockingQueue<ConsumerRecords<String, String>> queue = new LinkedBlockingQueue<>(100);

// Consumer thread
Thread consumerThread = new Thread(() -> {
    try (KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props)) {
        consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

        while (!Thread.interrupted()) {
            ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
            if (!records.isEmpty()) {
                queue.put(records);
            }
        }
    }
});

// Worker threads
ExecutorService workers = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(numWorkers);
for (int i = 0; i < numWorkers; i++) {
    workers.submit(() -> {
        while (!Thread.interrupted()) {
            try {
                ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = queue.poll(1, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
                if (records != null) {
                    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
                        processRecord(record);
                    }
                }
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                break;
            }
        }
    });
}

consumerThread.start();
// ... later ...
consumerThread.interrupt();
workers.shutdown();
workers.awaitTermination(1, TimeUnit.MINUTES);
```

### Pattern 5: Pause/Resume for Flow Control

```java
Map<TopicPartition, Long> targetOffsets = new HashMap<>();

consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

while (true) {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));

    // Check lag and pause fast partitions
    for (TopicPartition partition : consumer.assignment()) {
        long position = consumer.position(partition);
        long lag = consumer.currentLag(partition).orElse(0);

        if (lag > MAX_LAG) {
            consumer.pause(Collections.singleton(partition));
        } else {
            consumer.resume(Collections.singleton(partition));
        }
    }

    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
        processRecord(record);
    }
}
```

### Pattern 6: Manual Partition Assignment for Stateful Processing

```java
String topic = "events";
// Manually assign specific partitions
TopicPartition partition0 = new TopicPartition(topic, 0);
TopicPartition partition1 = new TopicPartition(topic, 1);

consumer.assign(Arrays.asList(partition0, partition1));

// Restore position from local state store
consumer.seek(partition0, localStore.getOffset(partition0));
consumer.seek(partition1, localStore.getOffset(partition1));

while (true) {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));

    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
        processRecord(record);
        localStore.updateOffset(record.partition(), record.offset() + 1);
    }
}
```

### Pattern 7: Transactional Message Consumption

```java
props.setProperty("isolation.level", "read_committed");

try (KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props)) {
    consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

    while (true) {
        ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));

        // Only committed transactional messages are returned
        for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
            // Safe to process; definitely committed
            processRecord(record);
        }

        consumer.commitSync();
    }
}
```

### Best Practices

1. **Always close**: Use try-with-resources or finally block
2. **One thread per consumer**: Never share between threads
3. **Handle CommitFailedException**: Indicates need to rejoin group
4. **Tune max.poll.interval.ms**: Based on expected processing time
5. **Use committed offset semantics**: Commit = next offset to consume
6. **Handle rebalances**: Implement ConsumerRebalanceListener properly
7. **Avoid long processing**: Move to separate threads if needed
8. **Monitor lag**: Use `currentLag()` or metrics
9. **Test exception paths**: Simulate broker failures, network issues
10. **Log poll loop latency**: Detect slow polls indicating problems

